obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (27570)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27570&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Legal Services Authorities`
  line `Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India, ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line `and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and for different States, and any`
  line `reference to commencement in any provision of this Act in relation to any State shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to the commencement of that provision in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `2. 9th November, 1995, vide notification No. S.O. 893(E), dated 9th November, 1995, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (27571)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27571&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) “case” includes a suit or any proceeding before a court;`
  line
  line `(aa) “Central Authority” means the National Legal Services Authority constituted under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(aaa) “court” means a civil, criminal or revenue court and includes any tribunal or any other`
  line `authority constituted under any law for the time being in force, to exercise judicial or quasi-judicial`
  line functions;]
  line
  line `(b) “District Authority” means a District Legal Services Authority constituted under section 9;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(bb) “High Court Legal Services Committee” means a High Court Legal Services Committee`
  line `constituted under section 8A;]`
  line
  line `(c) “legal service” includes the rendering of any service in the conduct of any case or other legal`
  line `proceeding before any court or other authority or tribunal and the giving of advice on any legal`
  line matter;
  line
  line `(d) “Lok Adalat” means a Lok Adalat organised under Chapter VI;`
  line
  line `(e) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ff) “regulations” means regulations made under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(g) “scheme” means any scheme framed by the Central Authority, a State Authority or a District`
  line `Authority for the purpose of giving effect to any of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) “State Authority” means a State Legal Services Authority constituted under section 6;`
  line
  line `(i) “State Government” includes the administrator of a Union territory appointed by the President`
  line `under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(j) “Supreme Court Legal Services Committee” means the Supreme Court Legal Services`
  line `Committee constituted under section 3A;`
  line
  line `(k) “Taluk Legal Services Committee” means a Taluk Legal Services Committee constituted`
  line `under section 11A.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any other enactment or any provision thereof shall, in relation to an`
  line `area in which such enactment or provision is not in force, be construed as a reference to the corresponding`
  line `law or the relevant provision of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 2, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (27572)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the National Legal Services Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for section 3 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27572&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3. Constitution of the National Legal Services Authority.—(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute a body to be called the National Legal Services Authority to exercise the powers and perform`
  line `the functions conferred on, or assigned to, the Central Authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Authority shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Justice of India who shall be the Patron-in-Chief;`
  line
  line `(b) a serving or retired Judge of the Supreme Court to be nominated by the President, in`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of India, who shall be the Executive Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(c) such number of other members, possessing such experience and qualifications, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, to be nominated by that Government in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall, in consultation with the Chief Justice of India, appoint a person to`
  line `be the Member-Secretary of the Central Authority, possessing such experience and qualifications as may`
  line `be prescribed by that Government, to exercise such powers and perform such duties under the Executive`
  line `Chairman of the Central Authority as may be prescribed by that Government or as may be assigned to`
  line `him by the Executive Chairman of that Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of members and the Member-Secretary`
  line `of the Central Authority shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation`
  line `with the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Authority may appoint such number of officers and other employees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, in consultation with the Chief Justice of India, for the efficient`
  line `discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers and other employees of the Central Authority shall be entitled to such salary and`
  line `allowances and shall be subject to such other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(7) The administrative expenses of the Central Authority, including the salaries, allowances and`
  line `pensions payable to the Member-Secretary, officers and other employees of the Central Authority, shall`
  line `be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  line
  line `(8) All orders and decisions of the Central Authority shall be authenticated by the Member-Secretary`
  line `or any other officer of the Central Authority duly authorised by the Executive Chairman of that Authority.`
  line
  line `(9) No act or proceeding of the Central Authority shall be invalid merely on the ground of the`
  line `existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Central Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (27573)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Supreme Court Legal Services Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27573&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall constitute a`
  line `committee to be called the Supreme Court Legal Services Committee for the purpose of exercising such powers and performing such functions as may be determined by regulations made by the Central`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) a sitting Judge of the Supreme Court who shall be the Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other members possessing such experience and qualifications as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `to be nominated by the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Justice of India shall appoint a person to be the Secretary to the Committee, possessing`
  line `such experience and qualifications as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of the members and Secretary of the`
  line `Committee shall be such as may be determined by regulations made by the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Committee may appoint such number of officers and other employees as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government, in consultation with the Chief Justice of India, for the efficient discharge of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers and other employees of the Committee shall be entitled to such salary and allowances`
  line `and shall be subject to such other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Central Government`
  line `in consultation with the Chief Justice of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (27574)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions of the Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27574&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Authority shall ^1`
  line `*** perform all or any of the`
  line `following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) lay down policies and principles for making legal services available under the provisions of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) frame the most effective and economical schemes for the purpose of making legal services`
  line `available under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) utilise the funds at its disposal and make appropriate allocations of funds to the State`
  line `Authorities and District Authorities;`
  line
  line `(d) take necessary steps by way of social justice litigation with regard to consumer protection,`
  line `environmental protection or any other matter of special concern to the weaker sections of the society`
  line `and for this purpose, give training to social workers in legal skills;`
  line
  line `(e) organise legal aid camps, especially in rural areas, slums or labour colonies with the dual`
  line `purpose of educating the weaker sections of the society as to their rights as well as encouraging the`
  line `settlement of disputes through Lok Adalats;`
  line
  line `(f) encourage the settlement of disputes by way of negotiations, arbitration and conciliation;`
  line
  line `(g) undertake and promote research in the field of legal services with special reference to the need`
  line `for such services among the poor;`
  line
  line `(h) to do all things necessary for the purpose of ensuring commitment to the fundamental duties`
  line `of citizens under Part IVA of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(i) monitor and evaluate implementation of the legal aid programmes at periodic intervals and`
  line `provide for independent evaluation of programmes and schemes implemented in whole or in part by`
  line `funds provided under this Act;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(j) provide grants-in-aid for specific schemes to various voluntary social service institutions and`
  line `the State and District Authorities, from out of the amounts placed at its disposal for the`
  line `implementation of the legal services schemes under the provisions of this Act;]`
  line
  line `(k) develop, in consultation with the Bar Council of India, programmes for clinical legal`
  line `education and promote guidance and supervise the establishment and working of legal services clinics`
  line `in universities, law colleges and other institutions;`
  line
  line `(l) take appropriate measures for spreading legal literacy and legal awareness amongst the people`
  line `and, in particular, to educate weaker sections of the society about the rights, benefits and`
  line `privileges guaranteed by social welfare legislations and other enactments as well as administrative`
  line `programmes and measures;`
  line
  line `(m) make special efforts to enlist the support of voluntary social welfare institutions working at`
  line `the grass-root level, particularly among the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes, women and`
  line `rural and urban labour; and`
  line
  line `(n) coordinate and monitor the functioning of ^3`
  line `[State Authorities, District Authorities, Supreme`
  line `Court Legal Services Committee, High Court Legal Services Committees, Taluk Legal Services`
  line `Committees and voluntary social service institutions] and other legal services organisations and give`
  line `general directions for the proper implementation of the legal services programmes.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words ", subject to the general directions of the Central Government," omitted by Act of 59 of 1994, s. 4`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 4, for clause (j) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "State and District Authorities and other voluntary social welfare institutions" (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (27575)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Central Authority to work in coordination with other agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27575&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `In the discharge of its`
  line `functions under this Act, the Central Authority shall, wherever appropriate, act in coordination with other`
  line `governmental and non-governmental agencies, universities and others engaged in the work of promoting`
  line `the cause of legal services to the poor.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (27576)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Constitution of State Legal Services Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for section 6 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27576&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[6. Constitution of State Legal Services Authority.—(1) Every State Government shall constitute a`
  line `body to be called the Legal Services Authority for the State to exercise the powers and perform the`
  line `functions conferred on, or assigned to, a State Authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Authority shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Justice of the High Court who shall be the Patron-in-Chief;`
  line
  line `(b) a serving or retired Judge of the High Court, to be nominated by the Governor, in consultation`
  line `with the Chief Justice of the High Court, who shall be the Executive Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(c) such number of other members, possessing such experience and qualifications as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, to be nominated by that Government in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court, appoint a`
  line `person belonging to the State Higher Judicial Service, not lower in rank than that of a District Judge, as`
  line `the Member-Secretary of the State Authority, to exercise such powers and perform such duties under the`
  line `Executive Chairman of the State Authority as may be prescribed by that Government or as may be`
  line `assigned to him by the Executive Chairman of that Authority.`
  line
  line `Provided that a person functioning as Secretary of a State Legal Aid and Advice Board immediately`
  line `before the date of constitution of the State Authority may be appointed as Member-Secretary of that`
  line `Authority, even if he is not qualified to be appointed as such under this sub-section, for a period not`
  line `exceeding five years.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of members and the Member-Secretary`
  line `of the State Authority shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government in consultation with`
  line `the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Authority may appoint such number of officers and other employees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court, for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers and other employees of the State Authority shall be entitled to such salary and`
  line `allowances and shall be subject to such other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(7) The administrative expenses of the State Authority, including the salaries, allowances and`
  line `pensions payable to the Member-Secretary, officers and other employees of the State Authority shall be`
  line `defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of the State.`
  line
  line `(8) All orders and decisions of the State Authority shall be authenticated by the Member-Secretary or`
  line `any other officer of the State Authority duly authorised by the Executive Chairman of the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(9) No act or proceeding of a State Authority shall be invalid merely on the ground of the existence of`
  line `any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the State Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (27577)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions of the State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27577&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the State Authority to give to effect`
  line `to the policy and directions of the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the functions referred to in sub-section (1), the State`
  line `Authority shall perform all or any of the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) give legal service to persons who satisfy the criteria laid down under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) conduct ^1`
  line `[Lok Adalats, including Lok Adalats for High Court cases];`
  line
  line `(c) undertake preventive and strategic legal aid programmes; and`
  line
  line `(d) perform such other functions as the State Authority may, in consultation with the ^2`
  line [Central
  line `Authority], fix by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 6, for "Lok Adalats" (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (27578)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `State Authority to act in coordination with other agencies, etc., and be subject to directions given by the Central Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sections 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27578&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[8. State Authority to act in coordination with other agencies., etc., and be subject to directions`
  line `given by the Central Authority.—In the discharge of its functions the State Authority shall`
  line `appropriately act in coordination with other governmental agencies, non-governmental voluntary social`
  line `service institutions, universities and other bodies engaged in the work of promoting the cause of legal`
  line `services to the poor and shall also be guided by such directions as the Central Authority may give to it in`
  line writing.
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (27579)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `High Court Legal Services Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27579&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority shall constitute a Committee`
  line `to be called the High Court Legal Services Committee for every High Court, for the purpose of exercising`
  line `such powers and performing such functions as may be determined by regulations made by the State`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) a sitting Judge of the High Court who shall be the Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other members possessing such experience and qualifications as may be`
  line `determined by regulations made by the State Authority,`
  line
  line `to be nominated by the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Justice of the High Court shall appoint a Secretary to the Committee possessing such`
  line `experience and qualifications as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of the members and Secretary of the`
  line `Committee shall be such as may be determined by regulations made by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Committee may appoint such number of officers and other employees as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court for the efficient`
  line `discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers and other employees of the Committee shall be entitled to such salary and allowances`
  line `and shall be subject to such other conditions of Service as may be prescribed by the State Government in`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (27580)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `District Legal Services Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27580&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court, constitute a body to be called the District Legal Services Authority for`
  line `every District in the State to exercise the powers and perform the functions conferred on, or assigned to,`
  line `the District Authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A District Authority shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) the District Judge who shall be its Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other members, possessing such experience and qualifications, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, to be nominated by that Government in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Authority shall, in consultation with the Chairman of the District Authority, appoint a`
  line `person belonging to the State Judicial Service not lower in rank than that of a Subordinate Judge or Civil`
  line `Judge posted at the seat of the District Judiciary as Secretary of the District Authority to exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties under the Chairman of that Committee as may be assigned to him by`
  line `such Chairman.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of members and Secretary of the District`
  line `Authority shall be such as may be determined by regulations made by the State Authority in consultation`
  line `with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(5) The District Authority may appoint such number of officers and other employees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers and other employees of the District Authority shall be entitled to such salary and`
  line `allowances and shall be subject to such other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(7) The administrative expenses of every District Authority, including the salaries, allowances and`
  line `pensions payable to the Secretary, officers and other employees of the District Authority, shall be`
  line `defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of the State.`
  line
  line `(8) All orders and decisions of the District Authority shall be authenticated by the Secretary or by any`
  line `other officer of the District Authority duly authorised by the Chairman of that Authority.`
  line
  line `(9) No act or proceeding of the District Authority shall be invalid merely on the ground of the`
  line `existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the District Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (27581)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of the District Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27581&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every District Authority to`
  line `perform such of the functions of the State Authority in the District as may be delegated to it from time to`
  line `time by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the functions referred to in sub-section (1), the District`
  line `Authority may perform all or any of the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) coordinate the activities of the Taluk Legal Services Committee and other legal services in`
  line `the District;]`
  line
  line `(b) organise Lok Adalats within the District; and`
  line
  line `(c) perform such other functions as the State Authority may ^2`
  line `*** fix by regulations`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 8, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line `2. The words ", in consultation with the State Government," omitted by Act 59 of 1994, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994)`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (27582)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `District Authority to act in coordination with other agencies and be subject to directions given by the Central Authority, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27582&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the District`
  line `Authority shall, wherever appropriate, act in coordination with other governmental and`
  line `non-governmental institutions, universities and others engaged in the work of promoting the cause of`
  line `legal services to the poor and shall also be guided by such directions as the Central Authority or the State`
  line `Authority may give to it in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (27583)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 14
  title `Taluk Legal Services Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27583&sectionno=11A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[11A. Taluk Legal Services Committee.—(1) The State Authority may constitute a Committee, to`
  line `be called the Taluk Legal Services Committee, for each taluk or mandal or for group of taluks or mandals.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) The ^2`
  line `[senior-most Judicial Officer] operating within the jurisdiction of the Committee who`
  line `shall be the ex officio Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of other members, possessing such experience and qualifications, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, to be nominated by that Government in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee may appoint such number of officers and other employees as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court for the efficient`
  line `discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(4) The officers and other employees of the Committee shall be entitled to such salary and allowances`
  line `and shall be subject to such other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the State Government in`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(5) The administrative expenses of the Committee shall be defrayed out of the District Legal Aid`
  line `Fund by the District Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 2002, s. 2, for "senior Civil Judge" (w.e.f. 11-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (27584)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 15
  title `Functions of Taluk Legal Services Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27584&sectionno=11B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `The Taluk Legal Services Committee may`
  line `perform all or any of the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) co-ordinate the activities of legal services in the taluk;`
  line
  line `(b) organise Lok Adalats within the taluk; and`
  line
  line `(c) perform such other functions as the District Authority may assign to it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (27585)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 16
  title `Criteria for giving legal services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27585&sectionno=12&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every person who has to file or defend a case shall be`
  line `entitled to legal services under this Act if that person is`
  line
  line `(a) a member of a Scheduled Caste or Scheduled Tribe;`
  line
  line `(b) a victim of trafficking in human beings or begar as referred to in article 23 of the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `(c) a woman or a child;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(d) a person with disability as defined in clause (i) of section 2 of the Persons With Disabilities`
  line `(Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996);]`
  line
  line `(e) a person under circumstances of underserved want such as being a victim of a mass disaster,`
  line `ethnic, violence, caste atrocity, flood, drought, earthquake or industrial disaster; or`
  line
  line `(f) an industrial workman; or`
  line
  line `(g) in custody, including custody in a protective home within the meaning of clause (g) of`
  line `section 2 of the Immoral Traffic (Prevention) Act, 1956 (104 of 1956), or in a juvenile home within`
  line `the meaning of clause (j) of section 2 of the Juvenile Justice Act, 1986 (53 of 1986), or in a`
  line `psychiatric hospital or psychiatric nursing home within the meaning of clause (g) of section 2 of the`
  line `Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987); or`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(h) in receipt of annual income less than rupees nine thousand or such other higher amount as`
  line `may be prescribed by the State Government, if the case is before a court other than the Supreme`
  line `Court, and less than rupees twelve thousand or such other higher amount as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government, if the case is before the Supreme Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1996, s. 74, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 7-2-1996).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 10, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (27586)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 17
  title `Entitlement of legal services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27586&sectionno=13&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Persons who satisfy all or any of the criteria specified in`
  line `section 12 shall be entitled to receive legal services provided that the concerned Authority is satisfied that`
  line `such person has a prima facie case to prosecute or to defend.`
  line
  line `(2) An affidavit made by a person as to his income may be regarded as sufficient for making him`
  line `eligible to the entitlement of legal services under this Act unless the concerned Authority has reason to`
  line `disbelieve such affidavit.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (27587)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Grants by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27587&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Central Authority, by way of grants, such sums of`
  line `money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (27588)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `National Legal Aid Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27588&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority shall establish a fund to be called the`
  line `National Legal Aid Fund and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) all sums of money given as grants by the Central Government under section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) any grants or donations that may be made to the Central Authority by any other person for the`
  line `purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any amount received by the Central Authority under the orders of any court or from any other`
  line source.
  line
  line `(2) The National Legal Aid Fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of legal services provided under this Act including grants made to State Authorities;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) the cost of legal services provided by the Supreme Court Legal Services Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) any other expenses which are required to be met by the Central Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (27589)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `State Legal Aid Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 12, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27589&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Authority shall establish a fund to be called the State Legal`
  line `Aid Fund and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) all sums of money paid to it or any grants by the Central Authority for the purposes of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(b) any grants or donations that may be made to the State Authority by the State Government or`
  line `by any person for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any other amount received by the State Authority under the orders of any court or from any`
  line `other source.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Legal Aid Fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of functions referred to in section 7;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) the cost of legal services provided by the High Court Legal Services Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) any other expenses which are required to be met by the State Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (27590)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `District Legal Aid Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27590&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every District Authority shall establish a fund to be called the`
  line `District Legal Aid Fund and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) all sums of money paid or any grants made by the State Authority to the District Authority for`
  line `the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) any grants or donations that may be made to the District Authority by any person, with the`
  line `prior approval of the State Authority, for the purposes of this Act;]`
  line
  line `(c) any other amount received by the District Authority under the orders of any court or from any`
  line `other source.`
  line
  line `(2) A District Legal Aid Fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of functions referred to in section 10 ^2`
  line `[and 11B];`
  line
  line `(b) any other expenses which are required to be met by the District Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (27591)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27591&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority, State Authority, or the District Authority`
  line `(hereinafter referred to in this section as 'the authority'), as the case may be, shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the income and`
  line `expenditure account and the balance-sheet in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authorities shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority concerned to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the auditing of the accounts of an Authority under this Act shall have the same rights and`
  line `privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `has in connection with the auditing of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to`
  line `demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the Authorities under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authorities, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually by the Authorities to the Central Government or the State Governments, as the case may be.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(5) The Central Government shall cause the accounts and the audit report received by it under`
  line `sub-section (4) to be laid, as soon as may be after they are received, before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government shall cause the accounts and the audit report received by it under`
  line `sub-section (4) to be laid, as soon as may be after they are received, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (27592)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Organisation of Lok Adalats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sections 19 and 20 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27592&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[19. Organisation of Lok Adalats.—(1) Every State Authority or District Authority or the Supreme`
  line `Court Legal Services Committee or every High Court Legal Services Committee or, as the case may be, Taluk Legal Services Committee may organise Lok Adalats at such intervals and places and for`
  line `exercising such jurisdiction and for such areas as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Lok Adalat organised for an area shall consist of such number of—`
  line
  line `(a) serving or retired judicial officers; and`
  line
  line `(b) other persons,`
  line
  line `of the area as may be specified by the State Authority or the District Authority or the Supreme Court`
  line `Legal Services Committee or the High Court Legal Services Committee, or as the case may be, the Taluk`
  line `Legal Services Committee, organising such Lok Adalat.`
  line
  line `(3) The experience and qualifications of other persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) for`
  line `Lok Adalats organised by the Supreme Court Legal Services Committee shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The experience and qualifications of other persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) for`
  line `Lok Adalats other than referred to in sub-section (3) shall be such as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(5) A Lok Adalat shall have jurisdiction to determine and to arrive at a compromise or settlement`
  line `between the parties to a dispute in respect of—`
  line
  line `(i) any case pending before; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any matter which is falling within the jurisdiction of, and is not brought before,`
  line
  line `any Court for which the Lok Adalat is organised:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lok Adalat shall have no jurisdiction in respect of any case or matter relating to an`
  line `offence not compoundable under any law.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (27593)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Cognizance of cases by Lok Adalats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27593&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in any case referred to in clause (i) of`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 19,`
  line
  line `(i) (a) the parties thereof agree; or`
  line
  line `(b) one of the parties thereof makes an application to the Court,`
  line
  line `for referring the case to the Lok Adalat for settlement and if such court is prima facie satisfied that there`
  line `are chances of such settlement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the court is satisfied that the matter is an appropriate one to be taken cognizance of by the Lok`
  line Adalat,
  line
  line `the Court shall refer the case to the Lok Adalat:`
  line
  line `Provided that no case shall be referred to the Lok Adalat under sub-clause (b) of clause (i) or`
  line `clause (ii) by such court except after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the parties.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any cither law for the time being in force, the Authority or`
  line `Committee organising the Lok Adalat under sub-section (1) of section 19 may, on receipt of an`
  line `application from any one of the parties to any matter referred to in clause (ii) of sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 19 that such matter needs to be determined by a Lok Adalat, refer such matter to the Lok Adalat,`
  line `for determination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no matter shall be referred to the Lok Adalat except after giving a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard to the other party.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any case is referred to a Lok Adalat under sub-section (1) or where a reference has been`
  line `made to it under sub-section (2), the Lok Adalat shall proceed to dispose of the case or matter and arrive`
  line `at a compromise or settlement between the parties.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Lok Adalat shall, while determining any reference before it under this Act, act with utmost`
  line `expedition to arrive at a compromise or settlement between the parties and shall be guided by the`
  line `principles of justice, equity, fair play and other legal principles.`
  line
  line `(5) Where no award is made by the Lok Adalat on the ground that no compromise or settlement could`
  line `be arrived at between the parties, the record of the case shall be returned by it to the court, from which the`
  line `reference has been received under sub-section (1) for disposal in accordance with law.`
  line
  line `(6) Where no award is made by the Lok Adalat on the ground that no compromise or settlement could`
  line `be arrived at between the parties, in a matter referred to in sub-section (2), that Lok Adalat shall advice`
  line `the parties to seek remedy in a court.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the record of the case if returned under sub-section (5) to the court, such court shall`
  line `proceed to deal with such case from the stage which was reached before such reference under`
  line `sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (27594)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Award of Lok Adalat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 16, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 29-10-1994),`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27594&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Every award of the Lok Adalat shall be deemed to be a decree of a`
  line `civil court or, as the case may be, an order of any other court and where a compromise or settlement has`
  line `been arrived at, by a Lok Adalat in a case referred to it under sub-section (1) of section 20, the court-fee`
  line `paid in such case shall be refunded in the manner provided under the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870).]`
  line
  line `(2) Every award made by a Lok Adalat shall be final and binding on all the parties to the dispute, and`
  line `no appeal shall lie to any court against the award.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (27595)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Powers of Lok Adalat or Permanent Lok Adalat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 37 of 2002, s. 3, for "Lok Adalat" (w.e.f. 11-6-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27595&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `22. Powers of ^1`
  line `[Lok Adalat or Permanent Lok Adalat.]—(1) The ^1`
  line `[Lok Adalat or Permanent Lok`
  line `Adalat] shall, for the purposes of holding any determination under this Act, have the same powers as are`
  line `vested in a Civil Court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the requisitioning of any public record or document or copy of such record or document from`
  line `any court or office; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers contained in sub-section (1), every ^1`
  line `[Lok Adalat`
  line `or Permanent Lok Adalat] shall have the requisite powers to specify its own procedure for the`
  line `determination of any dispute coming before it.`
  line
  line `(3) All proceedings before a ^1`
  line `[Lok Adalat or Permanent Lok Adalat] shall be deemed to be judicial`
  line `proceedings within the meaning of sections 193, 219 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and`
  line `every ^1`
  line `[Lok Adalat or Permanent Lok Adalat] shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for the purpose of`
  line `section195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (27596)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 27
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-6-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27596&sectionno=22A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1In this Chapter and for the purposes of sections 22 and 23, unless the context`
  line `otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Permanent Lok Adalat" means a Permanent Lok Adalat established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 22B;`
  line
  line `(b) "public utility service" means any—`
  line
  line `(i) transport service for the carriage of passengers or goods by air, road or water; or`
  line
  line `(ii) postal, telegraph or telephone service; or`
  line
  line `(iii) supply of power, light or water to the public by any establishment; or`
  line
  line `(iv) system of public conservancy or sanitation; or`
  line
  line `(v) service in hospital or dispensary; or`
  line
  line `(vi) insurance service,`
  line
  line `and includes any service which the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `in the public interest, by notification, declare to be a public utility service for the purposes of this`
  line Chapter.
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (27597)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 28
  title `Establishment of Permanent Lok Adalats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27597&sectionno=22B&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 19, the Central Authority or, as the case may be, every State Authority shall, by notification,`
  line `establish Permanent Lok Adalats at such places and for exercising such jurisdiction in respect of one or`
  line `more public utility services and for such areas as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Permanent Lok Adalat established for an area notified under sub-section (1) shall consist`
  line of—
  line
  line `(a) a person who is, or has been, a district judge or additional district judge or has held judicial`
  line `office higher in rank than that of a district judge, shall be the Chairman of the Permanent Lok Adalat;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) two other persons having adequate experience in public utility service to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government on the recommendation of the`
  line `Central Authority or, as the case may be, the State Authority,`
  line
  line `appointed by the Central Authority or, as the case may be, the State Authority, establishing such`
  line `Permanent Lok Adalat and the other terms and conditions of the appointment of the Chairman and other`
  line `persons referred to in clause (b) shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_c:
  sectionId (27598)
  sectionNo 22C
  orderNo 29
  title `Cognizance of cases by Permanent Lok Adalat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27598&sectionno=22C&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any party to a dispute may, before the`
  line `dispute is brought before any court, make an application to the Permanent Lok Adalat for the settlement`
  line `of dispute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Permanent Lok Adalat shall not have jurisdiction in respect of any matter relating to`
  line `an offence not compoundable under any law:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Permanent Lok Adalat shall also not have jurisdiction in the matter where`
  line `the value of the property in dispute exceeds ten lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government, may by notification, increase the limit of ten lakh rupees`
  line `specified in the second proviso in consultation with the Central Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) After an application is made under sub-section (1) to the Permanent Lok Adalat, no party to that`
  line `application shall invoke jurisdiction of any court in the same dispute.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made to a Permanent Lok Adalat under sub-section (1), it—`
  line
  line `(a) shall direct each party to the application to file before it a written statement, stating therein`
  line `the facts and nature of dispute under the application, points or issues in such dispute and grounds`
  line `relied in support of, or in opposition to, such points or issues, as the case may be, and such party`
  line `may supplement such statement with any document and other evidence which such party deems`
  line `appropriate in proof of such facts and grounds and shall send a copy of such statement together with`
  line `a copy of such document and other evidence, if any, to each of the parties to the application;`
  line
  line `(b) may require any party to the application to file additional statement before it at any stage of`
  line `the conciliation proceedings;`
  line
  line `(c) shall communicate any document or statement received by it from any party to the`
  line `application to the other party, to enable such other party to present reply thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) When statement, additional statement and reply, if any, have been filed under sub-section (3), to`
  line `the satisfaction of the Permanent Lok Adalat, it shall conduct conciliation proceedings between the parties`
  line `to the application in such manner as it thinks appropriate taking into account the circumstances of the`
  line dispute.
  line
  line `(5) The Permanent Lok Adalat shall, during conduct of conciliation proceedings under`
  line `sub-section (4), assist the parties in their attempt to reach an amicable settlement of the dispute in an`
  line `independent and impartial manner.`
  line
  line `(6) It shall be the duty of the every party to the application to cooperate in good faith with the`
  line `Permanent Lok Adalat in conciliation of the dispute relating to the application and to comply with the`
  line `direction of the Permanent Lok Adalat to produce evidence and other related documents before it.`
  line
  line `(7) When a Permanent Lok Adalat, in the aforesaid conciliation proceedings, is of opinion that there`
  line `exist elements of settlement in such proceedings which may be acceptable to the parties, it may formulate`
  line `the terms of a possible settlement of the dispute and give to the parties concerned for their observations`
  line `and in case the parties reach at an agreement on the settlement of the dispute, they shall sign the`
  line `settlement agreement and the Permanent Lok Adalat shall pass an award in terms thereof and furnish a`
  line `copy of the same to each of the parties concerned.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the parties fail to reach at an agreement under sub-section (7), the Permanent Lok Adalat`
  line `shall, if the dispute does not relate to any offence, decide the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_d:
  sectionId (27599)
  sectionNo 22D
  orderNo 30
  title `Procedure of Permanent Lok Adalat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27599&sectionno=22D&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content:
  string
  line `The Permanent Lok Adalat shall, while conducting`
  line `conciliation proceedings or deciding a dispute on merit under this Act, be guided by the principles of`
  line `natural justice, objectivity, fair play, equity and other principles of justice, and shall not be bound by the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_e:
  sectionId (27600)
  sectionNo 22E
  orderNo 31
  title `Award of Permanent Lok Adalat to be final.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27600&sectionno=22E&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every award of the Permanent Lok Adalat`
  line `under this Act made either on merit or in terms of a settlement agreement shall be final and binding on all`
  line `the parties thereto and on persons claiming under them.`
  line
  line `(2) Every award of the Permanent Lok Adalat under this Act shall be deemed to be a decree of a civil`
  line court.
  line
  line `(3) The award made by the Permanent Lok Adalat under this Act shall be by a majority of the persons`
  line `constituting the Permanent Lok Adalat.`
  line
  line `(4) Every award made by the Permanent Lok Adalat under this Act shall be final and shall not be`
  line `called in question in any original suit, application or execution proceeding.`
  line
  line `(5) The Permanent Lok Adalat may transmit any award made by it to a civil court having local`
  line `jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if it were a decree made by that court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_e_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (27601)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 32
  title `Members and staff of Authorities, Committees and Lok Adalats to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27601&sectionno=23&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[23. Members and staff of Authorities, Committees and Lok Adalats to be public`
  line `servants.—The members including Member-Secretary or, as the case may be, Secretary of the Central`
  line `Authority, the State Authority, the District Authorities, the Supreme Court Legal Services Committee,`
  line `High Court Legal Services Committees, Taluk Legal Services Committees and officers and other`
  line `employees of such Authorities, Committees and the ^2`
  line `[members of the Lok Adalats] or the persons`
  line `constituting Permanent Lok Adalats shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 17, for sections 23 and 24 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994),`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 2002, s. 5, for "members of the Lok Adalats" (w.e.f. 11-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (27602)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 33
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27602&sectionno=24&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against—`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Patron-in-Chief, Executive Chairman, members of, Member-Secretary or officers or other`
  line `employees of the Central Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) Patron-in-Chief, Executive Chairman, member, Member-Secretary or officers or other`
  line `employees of the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(d) Chairman, Secretary, members or officers or other employees of the Supreme Court Legal`
  line `Services Committee, High Court Legal Services Committees, Taluk Legal Services Committees or`
  line `the District Authority; or`
  line
  line `(e) any other person authorised by any of the Patron-in-Chief, Executive Chairman, Chairman,`
  line `Member, Member-Secretary referred to in sub-clauses (b) to (d),`
  line
  line `for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `rule or regulation made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (27603)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 34
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27603&sectionno=25&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (27604)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27604&sectionno=26&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date on`
  line `which this Act receives the assent of the President.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (27605)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27605&sectionno=27&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[27. Power of Central Government to make rules.—(1) The Central Government in consultation`
  line `with the Chief Justice of India may, by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the number, experience and qualifications of other members of the Central Authority under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section3;`
  line
  line `(b) the experience and qualifications of the Member-Secretary of the Central Authority and his`
  line `powers and functions under sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of members and Member-Secretary of`
  line `the Central Authority under sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of officers and other employees of the Central Authority under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions of service and the salary and allowances of officers and other employees of the`
  line `Central Authority under sub-section (6) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) the number, experience and qualifications of members of the Supreme Court Legal Services`
  line `Committee under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 3A;`
  line
  line `(g) the experience and qualifications of Secretary of the Supreme Court Legal Services`
  line `Committee under sub-section (3) of section 3A;`
  line
  line `(h) the number of officers and other employees of the Supreme Court Legal Services Committee`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 3A and the conditions of service and the salary and allowances`
  line `payable to them under sub-section (6) of that section;`
  line
  line `(i) the upper limit of annual income of a person entitling him to legal services under clause (h) of`
  line `section 12, if the case is before the Supreme Court;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which the accounts of the Central Authority, the State Authority or the District`
  line `Authority shall be maintained under section 18;`
  line
  line `(k) the experience and qualifications of other persons of the Lok Adalats organised by the`
  line `Supreme Court Legal Services Committee specified in sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) other matters under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(la) the other terms and conditions of appointment of the Chairman and other persons under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 22B;]`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 1994, s. 18, for sections 27, 28 and 29 (w.e.f. 29-10-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 37 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 11-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (27606)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27606&sectionno=28&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government in consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of the High Court may, by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the number, experience and qualifications of other members of the State Authority under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and functions of the Member-Secretary of the State Authority under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of members and Member-Secretary of`
  line `the State Authority under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the number of officers and other employees of the State Authority under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions of service and the salary and allowances of officers and other employees of the`
  line `State Authority under sub-section (6) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the experience and qualifications of Secretary of the High Court Legal Services Committee`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(g) the number of officers and other employees of the High Court Legal Services Committee`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 8A and the conditions of service and the salary and allowances`
  line `payable to them under sub-section (6) of that section;`
  line
  line `(h) the number, experience and qualifications of members of the District Authority under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(i) the number of officers and other employees of the District Authority under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `(j) the conditions of service and the salary and allowances of the officers and other employees of`
  line `the District Authority under sub-section (6) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(k) the number, experience and qualifications of members of the Taluk Legal Services Committee`
  line `under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 11A;`
  line
  line `(l) the number of officers and other employees of the Taluk Legal Services Committee under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 11A;`
  line
  line `(m) the conditions of service and the salary and allowances of officers and other employees of the`
  line `Taluk Legal Services Committee under sub-section (4) of section 11A;`
  line
  line `(n) the upper limit of annual income of a person entitling him to legal services under clause (h)`
  line `of section 12, if the case is before a court, other than the Supreme Court;`
  line
  line `(o) the experience and qualifications of other persons of the Lok Adalats other than referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (27607)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of Central Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27607&sectionno=29&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Authority may, by`
  line `notification, make regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provisions is necessary or expedient for the purposes of`
  line `giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the powers and functions of the Supreme Court Legal Services Committee under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3A;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of the members and Secretary of the`
  line `Supreme Court Legal Services Committee under sub-section (4) of section 3A.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (27608)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of State Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27608&sectionno=29A&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority may, by`
  line `notification, make regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provision in necessary or expedient for the purposes of`
  line `giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the other functions to be performed by the State Authority under clause (d) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and functions of the High Court Legal Services Committee under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(c) the number, experience and qualifications of members of the High Court Legal Services`
  line `Committee under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms of office and other conditions relating thereto, of the members and Secretary of the`
  line `High Court Legal Services Committee under sub-section (4) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(e) the term of office and other conditions relating thereto, of the members and Secretary of the`
  line `District Authority under sub-section (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) the number, experience and qualifications of members of the High Court Legal Services`
  line `Committee under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 8A;`
  line
  line `(g) other functions to be performed by the District Authority under clause (c) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 10;`
  line
  line `(h) the term of office and other conditions relating thereto, of members and Secretary of the Taluk`
  line `Legal Services Committee under sub-section (3) of section 11A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (27609)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 40
  title `Laying of rules and regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718&sectionId=27609&sectionno=30&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00003_198739_1517807322718
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made under this Act by the Central`
  line `Government and every regulation made by the Central Authority thereunder shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session, or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry`
  line `of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree`
  line `in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation`
  line `should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act by a State Government and every regulation made by a State`
  line `Authority thereunder shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
